Anonymous Fri 12 Jul 2024 19:08:42 No.67336034 Report
Quoted By:
Finished up Flames and Flour, I quite like how novel of a premise it is both in its story and romantic dynamic. The anthro being that much older and more experienced than the human isn't often done, and the near fairy tale presentation of baking a comically large bread for a dragon is a really cool premise. Though, I do kind of feel like for a short story that the author was trying to do too many things at once. Having to balance the romance setup with the bread baking premise and the protagonist's internal strife ends up with all of them feeling kind of rushed, with none of them feeling as satisfyingly executed as I would've hoped. Still a great story and an easy recommend, I just feel like the author should have either made it longer or chosen to focus on less things.
